
[1]enumeration

   ENUMERA'TION, n. [L. enumeratio.] The act of counting or telling a
   number, by naming each particular.

   1. An account of a number of things, in which mention is made of every
   particular article.

   2. In rhetoric, a part of a peroration, in which the orator
   recapitulates the principal points or heads of the discourse or
   argument.
